any ideas what to do in such situations where the PR failed, but the corresponding runner still runs but shows no output? :/
This has happened quite a few times lately.

The raw logs just say

2022-02-21T19:34:38.2949659Z Requested labels: macos-latest
2022-02-21T19:34:38.2949722Z Job defined at: rust-lang-ci/rust/.github/workflows/ci.yml@refs/heads/auto
2022-02-21T19:34:38.2949751Z Waiting for a runner to pick up this job...
2022-02-21T19:34:41.9673665Z Job is waiting for a hosted runner to come online.
2022-02-21T19:34:47.4649646Z Job is about to start running on the hosted runner: GitHub Actions 28 (hosted)
as if the entire process was killed because the job didn't start in time while failing to communicate that :/
this is probably upstream github trouble and is just a matter of retrying the build, unfortunately

If you look at the "Summary" page, you can see the cause:

Received request to deprovision: The request was cancelled by the remote provider.

From what I can tell, when GitHub decides to shut it down (for whatever reason), the logs are lost. I don't know why, when you click "view raw logs", it only shows those 5 lines. In the GUI you can click the steps that completed to see that it was actually running. It ran for 49m 15s before it was killed.

do you see anything for the step that is currently running?
I don't see anything there
just the yellow swirly thing and that's it
nah, that's what I mean is that the logs are lost
